<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Receive 2.4 billion Dollar Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Foreign governments and
international organizations have pledged to grant Vietnam more
than 2.4 billion U.S. dollars of official development assistance
in the 1998 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made at the fifth Vietnam Consultative Group
meeting, which closed in Tokyo Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
About 25 percent of this sum will be in the form of
non-refundable aid.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the closing session, Vietnam's Deputy Prime
Minister Nguyen Dinh Bin thanked the donors for their effective
assistance to his country and the Japanese government for its help
which ensured the success of the meeting. 
</P>
