<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Armenian PM Ends Six-Day France Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Armenian Prime Minister Robert
Kocharyan ended his six-day visit here on Friday after talking
with French President Jacques Chirac about the dispute over
High-Karabakh between Armenia and Azerbaijan.
</P>
<P>
Chirac appealed for Kocharyan to accept the proposal by the
Minsk Group, a group of mediators chaired by the United States,
Russia and France.
</P>
<P>
The group proposes a withdrawal of Armenian troops from the
one-fifth of the Azerbaijani territory they occupy, the return of
Azerbaijani refugees, and the lifting of blockade by Azerbaijan
upon Armenia and Karabakh.
</P>
<P>
Armenia and Azerbaijan are involved in a protracted conflict
over Karabakh, an Armenia-populated enclave which broke away from
Azerbaijan in the late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of people were killed in the conflict.
</P>
<P>
The mainly Moslem Azeris have been at odds with the Christian
Armenians for centuries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
