<HEADLINE> Heathrow Terminal Partially Working After Blaze </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 12 (Xinhua) -- London Heathrow's Terminal One
partially reopened this afternoon for flights after a major fire
broke out early in the morning in a burger bar.
</P>
<P>
The terminal, which mainly handles domestic flights, is now
open for all flights after departures began at 3 pm this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
But airport officials said passengers using the airport can
still expect severe delays.
</P>
<P>
The fire, which broke out around 4:40 am, swept through the
main terminal, causing extensive damage and bringing chaos to the
world's busiest international airport.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Heathrow airport, Mark Phillips, said later
this morning the fire had been extinguished but travel chaos
lasted for hours longer.
</P>
<P>
There were no reports of injuries, but officials said damage
appeared to be considerable.
</P>
<P>
British Airways Plc cancelled 100 outgoing flights and 120
incoming. Three inbound flights were diverted to Stansted
northeast of London and to Southampton in southern England.
</P>
<P>
Heathrow's other three terminals remained open but flights were
subject to delays and an estimated 30,000 people had seen their
flights disrupted by mid-morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
