<HEADLINE> Israeli Soldiers Detained for Mistakenly Entering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 12 (Xinhua) -- A group of Israeli soldiers
were detained today by Palestinian security forces in southern
Gaza Strip, Israeli state television reported.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli soldiers were detained because of a mistaken
intrusion of the Palestinian self-rule area, according to the
report.
</P>
<P>
An Israeli armed patrol in a military jeep took a wrong turn at
the Deir el-Balah junction in southern Gaza Strip, and entered the
Palestinian-controlled region.
</P>
<P>
They were stopped and detained for interrogation by Palestinian
security forces. Senior officers of both sides held hour-long
negotiations to secure the release of the Israeli soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The incident is believed to be the first since the Palestinians
began to exercise autonomy in Gaza Strip and some areas in the
West Bank in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
