<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Host 1st SAR Int'l Handball Invitational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 12 (Xinhua) -- The First Hong Kong Special
Administration Region International Handball Invitational
Tournament will be held from December 25 to December 28, it was
announced here on today.
</P>
<P>
Participating in the tournament will be teams from China,
Macao, Slovenia, Nigeria, Switzerland and Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
According to a draw here today, China has been pooled into
Group A with Macao and Slovenia while Group B consists of
Switzerland, Nigeria and Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
The group winners will vie for the tournament title, with
seconds placers for the 3rd place and third players for the fifth
places.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Amateur Handball Association (HKAHA) has decided
to invite four of China's national team players to join in the
local players for the tournament.
</P>
<P>
If such arrangement proved to be successful, the HKAHA will
consider recruiting players from China's inland to join in the
local team, an official said.
</P>
<P>
The Association decided to invite from China's inland a coach
for the local team. HKAHA officials declined to identify who had
been targeted, but confirmed that contacts were made during the
National Games staged earlier this year in Shanghai.  
</P>
</TEXT>
