<HEADLINE> IFAD Funds Nepal's Poverty Alleviation Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 12 (Xinhua) -- The International Fund for
Agricultural Development (IFAD) has agreed to provide a loan of
8.87 million U.S. dollars for implementing a poverty alleviation
project in Nepal, the country's official RSS news agency reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement signed today in Rome, the poverty
alleviation project for western Terai focuses on employment of
poor rural women through credit, irrigation and community
development, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
The Terai plain in southern Nepal is the country's major food
producer.
</P>
<P>
The IFAD has so far extended eight project loans totaling 93.6
million dollars to Nepal between 1978 and 1997 on highly
concessional terms. Now five projects have been completed and
three are underway, the RSS said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
