<DOCNO> XIE19971213.0019 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yemeni PM: Yemeni-Egyptian Higher Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni Prime Minister Faraj
Saeed Bin Ghanim said the fourth session of the Yemeni-Egyptian
Joint Higher Committee which ended here today yielded "fruitful"
results in various fields.
</P>
<P>
At the closing ceremony of the two-day session, the Yemeni
prime minister voiced appreciation for the concerted efforts
exerted by the two sides to achieve the satisfactory results.
</P>
<P>
The achievement from the session which was aimed at promoting
bilateral relations was the introduction of new areas that
constitute a solid foundation for bilateral cooperation, he said.
</P>
<P>
These new areas, particularly the economic ones, involve joint
ventures in the fields of investment, banks and free trade zones
in the Yemeni city of Aden and Port Said in Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Prime Minister Kamal El-Ganzouri said at the closing
session that "the political ties between the two countries
necessitated a quick action in the field of economy."
</P>
<P>
The two countries seek to boost economic cooperation on
bilateral, regional and international levels, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that during the session, both sides reached an
agreement on the establishment of a Sanaa-based Yemeni-Egyptian
bank.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian prime minister said that the two countries
highlighted their keenness on making progress on the road to the
Arab solidarity and integration in the economic fields.
</P>
<P>
El-Ganzouri arrived here Thursday, leading a delegation of
cabinet ministers and businessmen to the session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
