<HEADLINE> Britain's Royal Mail to Issue Diana Stamps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Royal Mail plans to
issue a set of stamps commemorating Princess Diana, a Royal mail
spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
"We have every intention of issuing the stamps, but no date has
been set yet," he said.
</P>
<P>
Princess Diana died in a car incident with her boyfriend on
August 31 in Paris.
</P>
<P>
The mail planned to issue the stamps in September but was put
on hold because Diana's family did not think the time was right.
</P>
<P>
British newspapers said the stamps could possibly be issued in
the New Year. 
