<HEADLINE> 92 Kilograms of Hashish Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Ninety-two kilograms of hashish
were seized recently in southeastern Turkey, the Anatolia News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Acting on a tip-off, Turkish gendarme searched a villager's
home near the town of Silvan, and found 65 kilograms of hashish.
</P>
<P>
According to the revelation of the villager, the gendarme
confiscated another 27 kilograms of the drug at the same village,
said the agency.
</P>
<P>
But the report did not say when the gendarme took the action.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is a key transit route of drug to Europe from the area
bordering Afghanistan and Pakistan. In 1996, Turkey seized 4.4
tonnes of heroin, or 40 percent of the world's total haul, 12.3
tonnes of hashish, 233 kilograms of opium, 13 kilograms of cocaine
and 1,157 kilograms of base morphine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
