<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Turkish Minister
of State Mehmet Batalli said today the Turkish government has a
keen interest in enhancing bilateral relations with Ethiopia,
particularly in areas of trade and investment.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, Batalli made the
remarks during talks here with an Ethiopian delegation led by
Kassahun Ayele, minister of trade and industry.
</P>
<P>
Turkish exports to Ethiopia do not reflect the real potential
of the Turkish economy in terms of both diversity and value,
Batalli said, adding Turkish imports from Ethiopia are also
limited to raw materials.
</P>
<P>
He urged the two sides to strive to expand their volume of
trade, variety of trade items and joint investments.
</P>
<P>
Kassahun on his part said that Ethiopia and Turkey enjoy long
standing historical and economic ties.
</P>
<P>
"These ties have been further strengthened when the two sides
signed in 1993 an agreement on trade, economic and technical
cooperation in Turkey," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian minister added that measures have also been
taken in various areas of the economy with a view to empowering
and encouraging the private sector and attracting foreign
investment.
</P>
<P>
The 18-member Turkish delegation led by Batalli arrived here
early today for a seven-day visit in Ethiopia. The Turkish guests
will hold talks with pertinent offices during their stay in the
east African country. 
</P>
