<HEADLINE> Tunisia, EU Sign Loan Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Tunisia and the European Union
(EU) signed here today an agreement under which the European
Investment Bank (EIB) will offer Tunisia a loan of 65 million
ECUs (80 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Tunisia-Africa News Agency reported that the loan will be
allocated to road projects in a bid to improve the country's
infrastructure and safety of roads and traffic in the framework
of the ninth five-year plan (1997-2001) for economic and social
development.
</P>
<P>
The document was signed by Tunisian Minister of International
Cooperation and Investment Mohamed Channouchi and Chief
of the EIB Mediterranean Department John Louis Biankerly.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
