<HEADLINE> Sino-Thai Joint Chicken Farm Goes Into Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, December 13 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-Thai joint chicken
farm, which cost nearly 42 million yuan, has gone into operation
recently in north China's Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Located in Qingxu County near the capital city of Taiyuan, the
chicken farm, the first modern facility of its kind in the
province, was jointly built by the Chia Tai Group of Thailand
and a local grain-processing plant.
</P>
<P>
With imported advanced chicken raising and hatching equipment,
the farm is expected to provide 1.8 million chickens a year at
present and up to six million in near future.
</P>
<P>
It aims to earn more than 20 million yuan in sales and 4.8
million yuan in profits a year.
</P>
<P>
A firm has been established jointly by Chia Tai Group
and the grain-processing plant to produce feed.
The firm has so far become the largest feed producer in
the province and has earned 180 million yuan in sales and two
million yuan in pre-tax profits this year.
</P>
<P>
Chia Tai Group has planned to invest more in the development of
local agriculture, ranging from feed production, livestock
breeding to deep-processing of farm produce.  
</P>
</TEXT>
