<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientists Praised By Vice-Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 13 (Xinhua) --Field workers of the Chinese
Academy of Sciences (CAS) were praised today for their hard work
and contributions to the country by Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also member of the Communist Party of China Central
Committee Politburo, told a group of scientists at CAS's second
conference on field work that they should make an effort to
inherit the tradition of seeking truth from facts and be
creative and devoted to make further progress in the utilization
of resources, environmental protection and agricultural
development.
</P>
<P>
Participants heard reports from the field by scientists about
developments in gold ore prospecting, grain output assessing,
restoration of the eco-system, and control of diseases on cotton
plants.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that over 10,000 field-workers from 50 CAS
institutes have made many discoveries in their research, and the
natural resources situation is now clearer, thanks to their
efforts, which have provided a large amount of data for
governmental decisions on industrial layout. 
</P>
</TEXT>
