<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Fruit Producer in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, December 13 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Shaanxi
Province has produced 4.2 million tons of fruit this year and
expects to become one of the country's four biggest fruit
producers, after ten years of work.
</P>
<P>
The acreage under fruit trees, which is now 733,000 ha., has
been growing by 20 percent annually in Shaanxi in recent years,
and the output of apples, pears and kiwi fruit by 24 percent.
</P>
<P>
The province produced 3.2 million tons of apple this year, or
nearly a fifth of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
The apple-growing acreage has gone from 47,000 ha. in 1985 to
533,000 ha now, making it the country's second largest apple
producer.
</P>
<P>
It also leads the country in kiwi fruit output, which is at
18,000 tons a year.
</P>
<P>
Its fruits are becoming popular in the regions of Hong Kong and
Macao and in some Southeast Asian countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
