<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Records Fall at World Weightlifting Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHIANG MAI, Thailand, December 13 (Xinhua) -- World records
fell at the hands of Chinese and Turkish strongwomen at the World
Weighlifting Championships here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
During the women's events, a total of five world records
tumbled in the 83 kilograms category to Derya Acikgoz of Turkey
and China's Tang Weifang.
</P>
<P>
Tang broke the world record by snatching 115kg and took the
gold with 117.5kg.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese lifter also broke the world record at her third
attempt in jerk with 143kg for the overall world record.
</P>
<P>
Acikgoz, who set the previous records in June at the European
championships in Seville, could only equal her former record of
115kg in the snatch to take the silver medal.
</P>
<P>
But she overcame the Chinese at her second attempt with 147.5kg
and setting a new world record in the category and overall with
262.5kg, improving on her Seville records by 5kg and taking the
two gold medals.
</P>
<P>
In the over 83kg category, China's Ma Runmei took two gold
medals with 145kg in the snatch and 252.5kg overall, far behind
the 260kg world record held by her compatriot Li Yajuan since 1993.
</P>
<P>
In the snatch, 18-year-old Aye Aye Aung of Myanmar, who weighs
107 kg, won a second gold medal by lifting 110 kg. Nigerian Musa
Balkisu took silver with 107.5 kg, the first medal for Africa.
</P>
</TEXT>
