<HEADLINE> Number Of Mobile Phone Users Increasing Sharply In Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, December 13 (Xinhua) -- The city of Quanzhou in east
China's Fujian Province has added 101,000 mobile phone customers
this year, bringing the total number to 202,000.
</P>
<P>
This indicates that not only the rich people and senior
leaders, but also the common folk, can afford these conveniences.
</P>
<P>
The city began to develop mobile telecommunications in 1991,
when it had only three base stations. The city had about 360
mobile phone customers a year later.
</P>
<P>
By June of this year, the handling capacity of the local mobile
telecommunications network, including digital and analog, had bee
at least 250,000 lines.
</P>
<P>
During the second half of the year, the province spent 1.5
billion yuan on its mobile telecommunications networks. The
number of base stations is expected to be 431 next year and
the handling capacity to be 600,000 lines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
