<HEADLINE> World Judo Champion Anno Wins in Fukuoka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 13 (Xinhua) -- World light heavyweight champion
Noriko Anno of Japan won the 78 kilograms title in the new
category system at the Fukuoka women's judo tournament on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Anno used a major inner reaping for an ippon
three minutes 53 seconds into the final to beat world silver
medallist Diadenis Luna of Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Japan and China took two titles each with Nami Kimoto, Qin
Dongya and Yuan Hua winning the 63kg, 70kg and over 78kg classes.
</P>
<P>
Qin defeated world champion Kate Howey of Britian by a
unanimous decision in the middleweight final, while Yuan downed
Japan's Yoshie Kiya with a one arm shoulder throw to win the
middleweight crown.
</P>
<P>
Kimoto, who shocked world champion Severine Vandenhende of
France in the semi-finals, threw down her compatriot Risa Kazumi
with a major outer reaping 15 seconds into the light middleweight
final for waza-ari and kept the lead to win the title.
</P>
<P>
The new classes, which were approved at the International Judo
Federation general assembly shortly before the Paris world
championships in October, are 48kg, 52kg, 57kg, 63kg, 70kg, 78kg,
and over 78kg in the women's competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
