<HEADLINE> Lloyd to Vie for Title Against Connors in Champions Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 13 (AXinhua) -- Britain's Davis Cup captain
John Lloyd will play Jimmy Connors in the final of the Champions
tennis tournament by beating Johan Kriek in Sydney on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 43-year-old Lloyd, who is yet to win one of the world
over-35's tournaments, won over the second seeded South African
Kriek 7-6 (7-3), 6-1.
</P>
<P>
The only other time Lloyd reached an over-35's final was in
Washington last year when he lost to Ecuador's Andres Gomez in
three sets.
</P>
<P>
Former world number one Connors battled back from 2-5 in the
first set to oust compatriot Tim Wilkison 7-6 (7-0), 6-3 in the
other semi-final. 
