<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Holds Promotion Fair for Non-Polluted Food </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 13 (Xinhua) -- A promotion fair that
presents more than 800 kinds of non-polluted food from all over
China opened today in Guangzhou, capital of south China's
Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
China started to advocate the production of non-polluted food
in 1990.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, the State Council, China's cabinet, approved the
establishment of a development center for non-polluted food.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the center showed that by the first half of
this year, over 820 kinds of non-polluted food have been developed
by more than 450 food producers across the country.
</P>
<P>
The four-day promotion fair is co-sponsored by the development
center, the Chinese Association of Non-Polluted Food and local
agricultural departments in Guangdong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
