<HEADLINE> Pak to Launch 2010 Program for Economic Uplift </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 13 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan will next month
launch a 2010 Program aimed at realizing economic and social
uplift through unprecedented community participation, a senior
official said today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a seminar on vocational guidance and career
planning here, Chief Coordinator of the Program Ahsan Iqbal said
that the main objective of the Program was to increase the per
capita income to 1,000 U.S. dollars from 480 dollars.
</P>
<P>
Under the Program, agricultural growth will be increased from 6
percent to 14 percent, Iqbal said.
</P>
<P>
He said urged the nation to work with dedication and honesty
for a prosperous future of the country.  
