positive effect on Lebanon's economy.
</P>
<P>
"The fact that more than 800 companies from the 54 member
countries of the OIC will participate in the event is a boost to
the country's economy," he said.
</P>
<P>
The ITF is scheduled to take place at the Rashid Karami
International Fair in the country's northern port city of Tripoli
in October, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Jaber said that the ITF also help improve bilateral relations
between Lebanon and the Islamic member countries, especially after
the landmark visit by Syrian President Elias Hrawi to Tehran
earlier this week where he held successful meetings with Muslim
leaders.
</P>
<P>
IFP President Albert Aoun said that the 1998 event, will
incorporate showcases for construction, food and agriculture,
clothing, arts and crafts, tourism and development and will
include an exhibition featuring the leading manufacturers of the
OIC," he said. 
