local newspaper The Monitor reported today.
</P>
<P>
Uganda's exports to India have also increased from 31,000 U.S.
Dollars in 1992-1993 financial year to one million U.S. Dollars
in 1995-1996 financial year, the paper quoted First Prime
Minister and Foreign Minister Eriya Kategaya as saying. Kategaya
made the remarks at a farewell dinner held for Gill Singh, the
Indian High Commissioner to Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The main Indian export items Uganda are textiles,
pharmaceuticals, paints, agro-chemicals, motor vehicles,
bicycles, solar energy equipments and jewelery.
</P>
<P>
India is one of Uganda's main trade partners and it is also
the number one host country for Ugandan students. Over 400
students are studying in India and the number is on increase.
