<HEADLINE> Uganda to Extract Own Paste Additive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 13 (Xinhua) -- Uganda is planning to extract
a paste additive from Omutete, a local tree, for toothpaste.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian company, Kato Armoatic planned to provide boilers to
the manufacturers, said Ismail Tamale, the commercial manager of
the Egyptian company.
</P>
<P>
The company plans to organize residents in rural areas to
distil the oil of the tree and purchase the oil as a additive for
Nile Toothpaste designed by Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni.
</P>
<P>
The oil is extracted by hydro-distillation and condensation
processes, Tamele added.
</P>
<P>
Nile Toothpaste is the only toothpaste to be produced in
Uganda with natural ingredients.
</P>
<P>
Omutete is used by local herbalists for treating purpose.
