<HEADLINE> India's Tea Exports to Touch 180 Million Kg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 13 (Xinhua) -- India's tea exports would
touch the target of 180 million kg this year, Tea Board Chairman
S.S. Ahuja said today.
</P>
<P>
India's tea exports, which stood at 154 million kg last year,
are all set to increase with Indian tea making fresh inroads into
traditional markets such as Russia, the United Kingdom, Iran,
Canada, Japan and the United States, he said in his address to the
15th annual general meeting of Indian Tea Association in Calcutta.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistan market would act as a spring board to gain access
to other central Asian countries. Pakistan itself had placed
import orders of 2.5 million kg tea during the current year, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He urged the tea industry in the country to move towards
product diversification and develop more sophisticated packaging
infrastructure to compete in new markets.  
