<HEADLINE> Missing Myanmar Fishermen Reach Indian Shores </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 13 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen Myanmar fishermen,
who reportedly went missing after being caught in a recent
cyclonic storm in the Bay of Bengal, safely reached India's
southern shores on the Kerala Coast Friday evening, the Press
Trust of India (PTI) reported today.
</P>
<P>
The fishermen, who set sail on a motorized boat near Yangon,
Myanmar 45 days ago, lost their way in the severe cyclonic storm.
</P>
<P>
After running out of their food stocks, the fishermen had lost
all hopes of survival before they saw the faint glimmer of a
lighthouse at the Mamallapuram of India, which guided them ashore,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
All the fishermen were healthy but appeared exhausted, police
said.
</P>
<P>
As none of them possessed any passports or valid documents, a
case had been registered under the Foreigners Act. India's
Immigration Department and the Myanmar Embassy in New Delhi had
also been informed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
