<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe, S. Africa Cooperate in Building Railway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 13 (Xinhua) -- A tripartite agreement has
been signed by the Zimbabwean government, Zimbabwe's
Beitbridge/Bulawayo Railway (BBR) and Spoornet of South Africa
for construction of the railway line linking Beitbridge and west
Nicholson in South Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement signed in Zimbabwe on Friday, BBR will
build the 160 km line and provide all the rail infrastructure on
which Spoornet will operate passenger and goods trains.
</P>
<P>
Work on the 1.2 billion Zimbabwean Dollars (80 million U.S.
Dollars) rail line will start in the next three weeks.
</P>
<P>
The project will not only provide the railway companies in
Zimbabwe, Zambia, South Africa and the Democratic Republic of
Congo with a shorter route via Bulawayo, Zimbabwe's second
largest city, but will also enhance the rail service between
South Africa and her neighbors.
</P>
<P>
"This is the beginning of a future in the Southern African
Development Community and it is our desire to link Cameroon and
the rest of north Africa by rail," said Chief Executive of
Spoornet Mafika Mkwananzi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
