<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT December 13 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Senior U.S. and Chinese defense officials
Saturday initialed an agreement designed to prevent naval
accidents at sea as they ended the first-ever formal defense
consultations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Maritime Military Consultative Agreement was worked out
during Chinese President Jiang Zemin's visit to Washington in
October.
</P>
<P>
The two-day defense talks also yielded an agreement on
exchanging information on their military's role in humanitarian
relief missions. (US-China-Military)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Syrian Foreign Minister Farouk Al Shara has hailed the
Islamic Summit hosted by Tehran as an opportunity to put
Arab-Iranian ties back on track and remove misunderstandings
between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Egyptian TV program Beit Al Arab Friday
night, Shara said that the three-day summit, which wound up
Thursday, underscored the importance for Arab countries and Iran
to be in one camp against threats against security and stability
of the region.
</P>
<P>
He highlighted the importance of Iran's geographic site for
Arab national security. (Egypt-Syria-Iran)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GENEVA -- Leaders of the World Trade Organization (WTO) and the
European Union (EU) voiced their hope Sunday that China will join
the WTO as early as possible.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference following the reaching of the Agreement
on Financial Services, WTO Director-General Renato Ruggiero said
he shares the wish that China will be, in the next two years, a
member of the WTO and it "will participate in the negotiation or
the process of the liberalization by making a good offer."
</P>
<P>
"We also share the hope that China will at the earlier possible
date become a member of the WTO," said European Commission Vice
President Sir Leon Brittan. (WTO-China)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GENEVA -- The successful conclusion of negotiations on
financial services today has made 1997 a golden year of the
international trading system, said Renato Ruggiero,
Director-General of the World Trade Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
"This landmark agreement comes at a critical time," Ruggiero
told reporters.
</P>
<P>
With the Agreement on Financial Services, the WTO has reached
three agreements of historic importance in a year. It reached the
Agreement on Basic Telecommunications Services on February 15 and
the Information Technology Agreement on March 26. (WTO-Financial
Services)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GENEVA -- Seventy members of the World Trade Organization
reached an agreement on financial services here early this morning.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was made four hours behind the original deadline
of 23:00 GMT on December 12. The negotiations were part of the
unfinished business of the Uruguay Round (1986-1993) of
multilateral trade negotiations concluded in 1993.
</P>
<P>
The results of the negotiation concluded today will be part of
a protocol which will be open for governments to accept until
January 29, 1999. The agreement will enter into force on March 1,
1999 at the latest. (Geneva-Agreement Reached)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
