LUANDA -- A French company has found an oil field in Angola
with deposits exceeding 100 million tons in the deep sea near
Luanda.
</P>
<P>
According to a communique jointly issued by French Elf
Aquitaine Petroleum Company and Angola's State Petroleum Company,
the oil field, located at a 1250-meter deep sea bed area, 200 km
northeastern of Luanda, has great commercial potential.
</P>
<P>
The French company has 35 percent of the share for the
newly-found oil field. Some other foreign companies, mostly from
Europe, are also involved in tapping the oil field. (Angola-Oil
Field) 
