<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 13 (Xinhua) -- Beijing top party official
pledged here today that his municipality will strive to become
China's foremost city in promotion of socialist ethics and
cultural progress over the next five years.
</P>
<P>
Jia Qinglin, secretary of the Beijing Municipal Party
Committee, made the remark at the ongoing week-long Eighth Beijing
Municipal Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) that
opened Friday.
</P>
<P>
To improve the citizens' quality, Jia said, effective measures
are required to be taken to educate people in Marxism, Mao Zedong
Thought and Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
The municipal Party secretary called for further education in
patriotism and socialist ethics and morality among the Beijing
citizens.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Beijing residents are urged to observe disciplines,
be ready to help others, respect the elderly and take good care of
their kids as well as building harmonious relationships between
the husbands and wives.
</P>
<P>
Jia promised to increase investment in education and vowed the
city's determination to further spread science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he called for strengthening cultural exchanges with
foreign countries and bringing prosperity to socialist literature,
culture and art.
</P>
<P>
Jia suggested setting up more booming cultural business groups
and turn his municipality into one of the country's most important
bases of cultural undertakings.
</P>
<P>
The city's service departments are also urged to provide more
and still better service. 
