<HEADLINE> New Oil Field Found in Angola Seas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, December 13 (Xinhua) -- A French company has found an
oil field in Angola with deposits exceeding 100 million tons in
the deep sea near Luanda.
</P>
<P>
According to a communique jointly issued by French Elf
Aquitaine Petroleum Company and Angola's State Petroleum Company,
the oil field, located at a 1250-meter deep sea bed area, 200 km
northeastern of Luanda, has great commercial potential.
</P>
<P>
The French company has 35 percent of the share for the
newly-found oil field. Some other foreign companies, mostly from
Europe, are also involved in tapping the oil field.
</P>
<P>
The communique said that it has been the third oil field Elf
Aquitaine has found in Angola. It has found a oil field with a
reserve of 660 million barrels in May 1996 and another with a
reserve of 700 barrels in August 1997.
</P>
<P>
The new founding is likely to increase the oil reserve Elf
Aquitaine explores by 20 percent.  
</P>
