<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 70 Participants Reach Agreement on Financial Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 13 (Xinhua) -- 70 participants reached an
agreement on financial services here early this morning.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was made over four hours behind the original
deadline of 23:00 GMT on December 12.
</P>
<P>
The negotiations were part of the unfinished business of the
Uruguay Round (1986-1993) of multilateral trade negotiations
concluded in 1993.
</P>
<P>
First offers to liberalize trade in financial services made
during the Uruguay Round were improved in 1995 in an interim
agreement which entered into force on September 1, 1996.
</P>
<P>
70 members (counting the European Communities as 15) of the
World Trade Organization (WTO) have taken part in the financial
services negotiations which began in April, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The total number of governments which have made commitments in
financial services under the General Agreement of Trade in
Services (GATS) is 102.
</P>
<P>
The results of the negotiation concluded today will be part of
a protocol which will be open for governments to accept until
January 29, 1999. The agreement will enter into force on March 1,
1999 at the latest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
