<HEADLINE> Myanmar Leader Leaves for ASEAN Summit in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 13 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Myanmar State
Peace and Development Council and Prime Minister Senior General
Than Shwe left here today for Malaysia to attend the Second ASEAN
Informal Summit scheduled to open in Kuala Lumpur Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for the Myanmar top leader to attend a
summit meeting of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN) since the country was admitted into the grouping in July
along with Laos.
</P>
<P>
The other seven members of the ASEAN are Brunei, Indonesia,
Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
