<HEADLINE> China to Examine and Register Environmental Auditors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 13 (Xinhua) -- China has formally launched
the examination and registration of the auditors on ISO-14000, a
set of international standards for environmental management, said
today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
A national registration committee for auditors of the
environmental management system, which has been set up under the
National Environmental Protection Agency (Nepa), is in charge of
the work, the English newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
The country's environmental protection management auditing is
to be unified under one set of standards, one system and one
certificate to better protect the environment, Zhang Xiaodan, an
official with the registration committee, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Statistics showed that about 55 enterprises across the country
have volunteered to carry out experimentation on the certification
and auditing of ISO-14000 since July 1996.
</P>
<P>
Zhang went on to say that the adoption of ISO-14000 benefits
not only the well-coordinated development of economy and
environment, but also helps to strengthen the government's
supervision on the enterprises' environmental management.
</P>
<P>
"It is also conducive to enhancing the enterprises'
competitiveness in the world trade market, improve their images
and increase their economic and environmental benefits," he added.
</P>
<P>
So far more than 120 countries have adopted and implemented the
ISO-14000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
