<HEADLINE> 319Kg Narcotic Drugs Seized in Myanmar in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 13 (Xinhua) -- A total of 319.7 kilograms of
narcotic drugs, including 9 kilograms of heroin and 262.73
kilograms of opium and other kinds of narcotic drugs, were seized
by the Myanmar authorities in the country in October, the official
daily the New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The seizure, made by the army units, police force and customs
departments, also included 31.525 liters of phensedyl, 1,250
kilograms of ammonium chloride and other liquid chemicals, and
143,900 tablets of amphetamine (stimulant drug).
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar authorities took action against 339 people in 326
drug-related cases in the month, the report said.
</P>
<P>
In September, over 486 kilograms of narcotic drugs were
confiscated in the country, according to an earlier official
report.  
</P>
