<HEADLINE> China-Made Electrical Appliances to Dominate Domestic Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese electrical appliances
will not only dominate the domestic market, but also will compete
on the international market by the year 2000, according to
economic predictions.
</P>
<P>
Experts and representatives from the 12 most popular electrical
producers attended a seminar here on development strategy oriented
to the new century.
</P>
<P>
Economists say that the sales ratio of domestic to imported
electrical products now is 8-2, exactly the opposite of a decade
ago. Domestic consumers now favor Chinese name brands.
</P>
<P>
The present achievement was attributed to massive reforms
carried out by large state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The Hi-Sense Group of Qingdao, specializing in computers, has
expanded its registered capital from 300 million yuan (37.5
million U.S. dollars) to 3 billion yuan (361 million US dollars)
with 24 subsidiaries set up in China and abroad. This year's sales
will top 5 billion yuan (602 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
One-third of the Haier Group's production and sales are outside
China.
</P>
<P>
Producers were told at the meeting that the central government
will continue its preferential policies. The Bank of China
recently granted an unprecedented bank loan of 3.8 billion yuan
(457 million U.S. dollars) to a state-owned Konca Color TV Group.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, experts warned these promising enterprises of the
need to upgrade the quality of their products.
</P>
<P>
Tomur Dawamat (Uygur), vice-chairman of the Standing Committee
of the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC), and Wu Changyuan,
vice-governor of Hainan Province, attended the meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
