<HEADLINE> China Scores Record Cotton Purchase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 13 (Xinhua) -- China's state purchase of
cotton harvested this year has reached a record height of 2.67
billion kilograms, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
By December 5, cotton purchased from the country's major cotton
planting areas has exceeded the total amount bought by the state
last year by 680 million kilograms, the paper quoted sources with
the All-China Federation of Supply and Marketing Cooperatives,
which is in charge of all state cotton purchases.
</P>
<P>
The city of Dafeng in east China's Jiangsu Province has set a
national record by selling over 50 million kilograms of cotton to
the state this year.
</P>
<P>
Northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, the
country's top cotton producer, is expected to harvest a total of
1.15 billion kilograms of cotton this year, and all the harvest
will be bought by the state.
</P>
<P>
It attributed this year's good cotton harvest to the
introduction of more advanced technology in cotton planting.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the government has taken a series of measures during
the purchasing to ensure the target of state cotton purchase is
met.
</P>
<P>
These measures include abolishing purchasing limits, increasing
purchasing standards, ensuring purchasing funds and monopolizing
the purchasing market and offering still better services.  
</P>
</TEXT>
