<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Plunges to New Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 13 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian rupiah plunged
to a historic low of 5,400 against the U.S. dollar Friday,
following what many analysts attributed to the announcement that
President Soeharto has called off his plan to attend an informal
ASEAN summit to be held early next week in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah was quoted at 5,400 against the dollar at 6:30 p.m.
before it recovered to 5,150/5,250 at 9:15 last night, dealers
said today.
</P>
<P>
The local currency has devalued by more than 100 percent since
the government floated the rupiah on August 14.
</P>
<P>
Minister/State Secretary Moerdiono announced here Friday that
the president's team of doctors advised him not to attend the
ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations) summit scheduled
for December 15-16.
</P>
<P>
Moerdiono, however, reiterated that the president was in good
condition and that his health has restored, but doctors advised
him against traveling.
</P>
<P>
Currency dealers also attributed the drop of the rupiah to
regional weaknesses which were driven by the falling South Korean
won.
</P>
<P>
The panic in the currency market spread to the Jakarta Stock
Exchange, which saw its composite index tumble 30.26 points to a
four-year low of 365.85.
</P>
<P>
All foreign investors dumped their local stocks when the rupiah
sank to another new low after the announcement that President
Soeharto would cancel his trip to Malaysia, brokers said today.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
