<HEADLINE> General Oviedo Surrenders to Paraguayan Justice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Paraguayan governing
Colorado Party presidential candidate Lino Oviedo surrendered to a
military unit in response to the arrest order issued by the
Paraguayan president.
</P>
<P>
Retired General Oviedo, who had eluded capture for the past 44
days, surrendered Friday to the First Infantry Division. He was
accompanied by his platform mate Raul Cubas, his defense counsel
and sympathizers.
</P>
<P>
Oviedo had been accused of aggravating President Juan Carlos
Wasmosy. Wasmosy forced Oviedo to retire by accusing him of
attempting a coup last April.
</P>
<P>
The former commander of the army and his followers consider
the arrest order part of a persecution campaign unleashed by
President Wasmosy, who is also a member of the Colorado Party.
</P>
<P>
Oviedo was nominated presidential candidate for next year's
general elections during the Colorado Party's primary held last
September. 
</P>
