<HEADLINE> Mexico's Motor Vehicle Output Grows 9.6% </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 12 (Notimex) -- Mexico's motor vehicle
total output reached 1,235,953 units from January to November of
1997, a 9.6 percent increase over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
These data were from a study made by the Mexican Motor
Vehicle Manufacturing Association (AMIA).
</P>
<P>
The study shows that the production of vehicles for the
Mexican domestic market in November was 317,232 units, 44.8
percent more than in the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Production for export reached 918,721 vehicles in the first
11 months of 1997, registering 1.2 percent increase as against
that in the same period last year. 
</P>
