<HEADLINE> Electricity for Guangdong Administrative Villages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 13 (Xinhua) -- The last group of 403
administrative villages in Guangdong Province, south China, now
have access to electricity, according to the provincial electric
power department.
</P>
<P>
The three-year effort to provide electricity to the villages
has been carried at a cost of some 200 million yuan (24 million US
dollars) accumulated from various channels.
</P>
<P>
Completion of the project is expected to greatly improve the
living standards of more than 800,000 villagers and promote
economic development in related rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong is the 14th Chinese province to provide power to all
administrative villages.
</P>
<P>
Power lines reached all towns and townships in the province by
1993.
</P>
<P>
The provincial goal to provide electricity to all remaining
villages in the near future.  
</P>
