<HEADLINE> Preliminary Work Completed on Shenzhen-Hong Kong Link </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, December 13 (Xinhua) -- Preparations for a cross-sea
highway bridge linking Shenzhen with the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) have been well under way, with the
hydrological and geographical exploration already completed.
</P>
<P>
The thoroughfare, known as the western passage, will stretch
from Shenzhen Bay to the northwestern part of Hong Kong to
alleviate heavy traffic.
</P>
<P>
On December 10 at a meeting here, experts from the Ministry of
Communications explained a report on the impact of water flow,
ports, and passing ships.
</P>
<P>
After hearing the report, Li Decheng, Shenzhen's vice-mayor,
underlined the importance of ensuring a smooth flow over the
western passage.  
</P>
