<HEADLINE> Nicaraguan Exports To Reach $800 Million in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Nicaraguan Exports will reach
800 million dollars by the end of this year, a 12 percent
increase over the value reached last year, said Friday the Center
for Export Procedures (Cetrex).
</P>
<P>
According to Cetrex, total exports had generated 713 million
dollars up to November 30.
</P>
<P>
"It is almost a sure thing that the 800 million dollars set as
a target for 1997 will be reached with this month exports," said
Ricardo Illeacas, Cetrex executive director.
</P>
<P>
The export value of non-traditional products by the end of
November had generated 411.8 million dollars, nine million dollars
more than the whole of last year, said Illescas.
</P>
<P>
Traditional products exports registered in the first 11 months
of this year were 301.3 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Within this context, sugar, coffee, and seafood show a good
performance, but cotton, beef and gold showed a drop in their
exports. 
</P>
