<HEADLINE> Two Brazilian Water Polo Players Fail Dope Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Two Brazilian water polo
players have tested positive for the anabolic steroid nandrolone,
the Brazilian Swimming Federation confirmed in Rio de Janeiro on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The pair were identified as Eric Borges and Alexandre Lopes,
the leading players of Brazilian water polo team.
</P>
<P>
The federation would await the results of follow-up tests on
Monday before deciding what action to take.
</P>
<P>
Borges and Lopes will stripped the rights to represent Brazil
for the World Swimming Championships in Perth, Australia next
January if the results are confirmed.
</P>
<P>
The news comes two weeks after the Brazilian federation gave a
four-year ban on the 100 meters butterfly national record holder
Hugo Duppre for positive-test. 
</P>
