<HEADLINE> German Economy to See 2.6 Percent Growth in 1998: Ifo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 12 (Xinhua) -- Germany's economy would continue
its current upswing and would expect a 2.6-percent growth in 1998,
the Ifo economic research institute predicted today.
</P>
<P>
According to the Munich-based institute, the increase in GDP
next year would be driven by a continued export boom as well as a
modest recovery in the domestic economy.
</P>
<P>
However, it also warned that the country's economy still lacks
a solid footing and is likely to be negatively affected by the
recent financial crisis in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Germany's unemployment could rise further to 4.45
million in 1998 compared with 4.39 million this year, the Ifo
said. 
</P>
