<HEADLINE> US Dollar Rises Against Japanese Yen, Other Currencies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 12 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar rose against
the Japanese yen and the German mark today, pushed up by positive
U.S. economic news and as several currencies in Asia hit record
lows.
</P>
<P>
In late New York trading, the dollar was quoted at 130.45
Japanese yen, up from 129.75 late Thursday. The dollar also was
changing hands at 1.7753 German marks, up from 1.7620.
</P>
<P>
The dollar also gained support from a strong U.S. bond market,
which rose following a government report of lower wholesale
inflation.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Labor Department reported that prices paid by
wholesalers dropped in November by 0.2 percent, the eighth drop
this year. The Producer Price Index has fallen at a 1.2 percent
annual rate through November.
</P>
<P>
The British pound was quoted at 1.6496 U.S. dollars, down from
1.6565 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Other late dollar rates in New York, compared with late
Thursday: 1.4335 Swiss francs, up from 1.4251; 5.9475 French
francs, up from 5.9010; 1,741.25 Italian lire, up from 1,725; and
1.4206 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4269. 
</P>
</TEXT>
